 :tx/rationale "Create task: COTX-6: E2E script results as store datoms — register E2E outcomes in the bilateral loop for F(S) contribution. BACKGROUND: The stale session bug analysis revealed that E2E scripts exercise lifecycle properties but their results are invisible to F(S) because they run outside the store. E2E scripts are the closest thing to Lifecycle-Bound Witnesses (LBW) — they bind multi-step workflows to temporal properties. If e2e_stage0_lifecycle.sh passes, that's evidence that INV-HARVEST-001 + INV-SEED-001 + INV-STORE-001 hold across the full lifecycle. But F(S) can't see this evidence. FIX: After each E2E script completes, register the outcome as store datoms: :e2e/script-name, :e2e/pass-count, :e2e/fail-count, :e2e/total-count, :e2e/run-at, :e2e/status (:e2e.status/pass or :e2e.status/fail), :e2e/traces-to (Ref to spec elements tested). Implementation: (1) Add a braid e2e register command that takes script name + results + spec refs. (2) Or: modify E2E scripts to call braid transact at the end with their results. (3) The bilateral loop's validation component reads :e2e/* entities as evidence alongside FBW witnesses. (4) F(S) increases when E2E scripts pass because more spec elements have lifecycle-level verification. This bridges the gap between unit-level FBW witnesses and system-level E2E validation. ACCEPTANCE: (A) E2E results stored as datoms. (B) F(S) validation component reads E2E results. (C) Passing E2E increases F(S). (D) Failing E2E does NOT decrease F(S) (it's evidence of a gap, not a regression). DEPENDS-ON: COTX-1 (t-222d6fdc). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/ (new e2e.rs or extend verify.rs) + bilateral.rs. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-WITNESS-001."
